## Required Output Format

Output the complete refined synthesis in XML:

```xml
<synthesis>
  <claims>
    <claim id="unique_id" agreement_level="consensus">
      <text>Claim text</text>
      <sources>
        <source id="source_id">
          <quote>Brief reference or placeholder — exact quote resolved later</quote>
        </source>
      </sources>
      <counterarguments>
        <counterargument>Counterargument if any</counterargument>
      </counterarguments>
    </claim>
  </claims>
  
  <areas_of_agreement>
    <item>Summary of agreed points</item>
  </areas_of_agreement>
  
  <areas_of_disagreement>
    <item>Summary of disagreements</item>
  </areas_of_disagreement>
  
  <uncertainties>
    <item>Identified uncertainties</item>
  </uncertainties>
  
  <needs_clarification>
    <item>Items needing expert clarification</item>
  </needs_clarification>
</synthesis>
```

**XML Formatting Rules**:
1. Output MUST be valid XML within `<synthesis>` tags.
2. Agreement levels: consensus, majority, divided, minority.
3. Ensure all tags are properly closed.

Include ALL claims and sections (existing + new). Use consistent IDs.


